	<div id="documentation">
		<h1 class="class">Operation</h1>

		<div id="description">
			<p>
Bankonet on Rails. Copyright &#169; 2011 <a
href="http://www.sqli.com">SQLI</a> <br /> Author: Philippe Gu√©gan (<a
href="mailto:pguegan@sqli.com">pguegan@sqli.com</a>)
</p>
<hr style="height: 1px"></hr><p>
An base class to represent any operation that can occurs on every account,
such as a debit or a credit.
</p>
<p>
An operation is bound to only one account. Each operation has an amount,
which is a decimal, with a scale of 2.
</p>
<p>
Every subclass should implement the method <tt>modify_account_balance</tt>
to alter the balance of the bound account, according to the amount of the
operation.
</p>

		</div>

